<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,310,1547,1573]" box="[189,310,1547,1573]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1547,1573]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1547,1573]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[187,1397,1594,1693]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
Differing from 
<taxonomicName authority="Block, 2022" authorityName="De Block" authorityYear="2022" box="[363,626,1594,1620]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Paracephaelis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aristata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[363,626,1594,1620]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Paracephaelis aristata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[631,719,1595,1621]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by having reddish brown bark (vs pale greyish or fawnish), glabrous lower leaf surfaces (vs densely covered with long erect or spreading hairs), and densely pubescent inner calyx surfaces (vs glabrous).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
